</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="202" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="9.[1436,2642,968,1746]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1438,1795,1437,1470]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. Van Zyl’s Golden Mole is found at only two locations (until recently, it was only known from a single location, but it was recorded from a second location near Groenriviermond in 2003) and has a small extent of occurrence (estimated to be just under 5000 km?) and small area of occupancy (estimated at only 32 km?®). Van Zyl’s Golden Mole might be severely threatened by habitat alteration from alluvial diamond mining and locally by construction of wind farms nearits type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
